The paper discusses the use of machine learning algorithms, particularly deep neural networks, in various domains where trustworthiness is a concern, including cyber-physical systems. This suggests that the paper could belong to the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), cryptography and security (cs.CR), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV), and systems and control (cs.SY). Among these categories, machine learning (cs.LG) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the use of ML algorithms and their limitations. Cryptography and security (cs.CR) is also likely as the paper discusses the generation of adversarial examples. Artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV) are also possible categories as the paper discusses the use of ML algorithms in perception and natural language processing. Finally, systems and control (cs.SY) is a possible category as the paper discusses the use of ML algorithms in cyber-physical systems.
